               <sec sec-type="bodytext">
                  <title>Marriage and Divorce: Research Starters Topic</title>
                  <p>Marriage is a social agreement between two or more persons that is sanctioned by religious law, civil law, or social norms, while divorce can be defined as an action or an instance of dissolving a marriage. The occurrence of divorce is inextricably linked to marriage practices in a given culture or society. There are numerous Research Starter articles related to this topic. The list below includes the most relevant Research Starter items.</p>
